# Multi-language (i18n)

This app supports **en / hi / kn** via `useTranslation()` and locale files under `src/data/seed/i18n/locales/`.

## Required for every UI change

1. **No hardcoded user-facing strings** in pages, components, or games (labels, titles, prompts, feedback, aria-labels, button text, empty states).
2. Add keys to **all three** locale files in the same change:
   - `src/data/seed/i18n/locales/en.json`
   - `src/data/seed/i18n/locales/hi.json`
   - `src/data/seed/i18n/locales/kn.json`
3. Use existing namespaces when possible: `common`, `launch`, `home`, `games`, `exam`, `feedback`, `learn`, `sideGames`, `lettersTable`, `maths`, `challenges`, `progress`.
4. Call `t('namespace.key', { vars })` — prefer real keys over English-only fallbacks for new copy.
5. Interpolation uses `{{varName}}` in JSON (e.g. `"Nice try! It was {{word}}"`).

## Allowed exceptions (not UI chrome)

- Learning **content** data: letter/word examples in subject JSON, English number-word curriculum for speech
- Technical identifiers: route paths, challenge IDs, CSS classes, log messages

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<title>Exam Practice</title>
correctMessage: 'Super star! You got it!'

// ✅ GOOD
title={t('games.examPractice.title')}
correctMessage={t('feedback.examCorrect')}
```

Before finishing a UI task, scan the diff for quoted English sentences and move them into locale JSON.
